ciscoMediaQualityMIB.name: ciscoMediaQualityMIB

revisions.description: Modified descriptions of cmqVideoCallActiveEntry and cmqVideoCallHistoryEntry.
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoMediaQualityMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-voice@cisco.com
ciscoMediaQualityMIB.description: This MIB module enhances the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB (RFC2128) by providing call information and voice and video quality statistics of call legs over a telephony and voice over IP network. *** ABBREVIATIONS, ACRONYMS AND SYMBOLS *** ASP - Acoustic Shock Protection MIC - Microphone MOS - Mean Opinion Score NR - Noise Reduction TDM - Time-Division Multiplexing VOIP - Voice Over IP

cmqVoIPCallActiveTable.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveTable
cmqVoIPCallActiveTable.description: This table is the VoIP extension to the callActiveTable of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice quality information and statistics for the VoIP call leg.

cmqVoIPCallActiveEntry.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveEntry
cmqVoIPCallActiveEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmqVoIPCallActiveTable. An entry into this table is created when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created which has corresponding callActiveInfoType equals to 'speech'. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

cmqVoIPCallActiveConnectionId.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveConnectionId
cmqVoIPCallActiveConnectionId.description: The global connection identifier for the active VoIP leg of the call.

cmqVoIPCallActiveCallReferenceId.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveCallReferenceId
cmqVoIPCallActiveCallReferenceId.description: The call reference ID associates the video call entry and voice call entry of the same endpoint. An audio-only call with a call reference ID of zero will not have a video call entry associated with it, although an audio-only call can also have a reference ID greater than zero.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCodecId.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCodecId
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCodecId.description: The codec type of the endpoint for the established voice path.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSevConcealRatioPct.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSevConcealRatioPct
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSevConcealRatioPct.description: The ratio of severely concealed seconds to the sum of unimpaired seconds and concealed seconds.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCallConcealRatioPct.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCallConcealRatioPct
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCallConcealRatioPct.description: The ratio of the recent concealment time to recent talk-mode time interval. The talk-mode interval is 3 seconds.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktLossRatioPct.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktLossRatioPct
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktLossRatioPct.description: The ratio of total effective received packet loss to the number of RTP packets expected.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxRoundTripTime.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxRoundTripTime
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxRoundTripTime.description: The round-trip delay is the sum of measured network delay plus transmit and receive endpoint processing delays.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCallDur.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCallDur
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxCallDur.description: Duration of receive path open from this peer to voice gateway for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxVoiceDur.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxVoiceDur
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxVoiceDur.description: Duration of speech received from this peer to voice gateway for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktLossConcealDur.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktLossConcealDur
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktLossConcealDur.description: The sum of error predictive concealment and bad protocol concealment in milliseconds.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntExpected.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntExpected
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntExpected.description: The expected number of packets to be received.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntNotArrived.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntNotArrived
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntNotArrived.description: The expected number of packets minus the number of received packets.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntComfortNoise.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntComfortNoise
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntComfortNoise.description: The number of received comfort noise packets for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntUnusableLate.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntUnusableLate
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntUnusableLate.description: The number of received voice packets that arrived too late to playout with CODEC (Coder/Decoder) during the call.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntDiscarded.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntDiscarded
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntDiscarded.description: The sum of the number of late packets and the number of bad protocol packets.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntEffLoss.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntEffLoss
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPktCntEffLoss.description: The total number of never-arrived packets and the number of discarded packets.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxUnimpairedSecOK.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxUnimpairedSecOK
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxUnimpairedSecOK.description: The cumulative number of seconds during which there was no concealment and is considered as OK seconds.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxConcealSec.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxConcealSec
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxConcealSec.description: The cumulative number of seconds during which there was some concealment.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSevConcealSec.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSevConcealSec
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSevConcealSec.description: The total number of seconds that are severely concealed from the start of the voice stream. A severly concealed second has more than 50ms of concealment.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufMode.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufMode
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufMode.description: The jitter buffer mode configured for the endpoint. adaptive (1): an adaptive size algorithm for jitter buffer, fixed (2): a fixed size algorithm for jitter buffer, unknown (3): an unknown size algorithm for jitter buffer, disabled (4): no jitter buffer is configured.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufNomDelay.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufNomDelay
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufNomDelay.description: The nominal jitter buffer playout delay in milliseconds configured for the endpoint.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufDlyNow.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufDlyNow
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufDlyNow.description: The playout delay buffer in milliseconds to accommodate interarrival jitter. The interarrival jitter is the network arrival jitter between consecutive frames measured at the receiver.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufLowWater.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufLowWater
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBufLowWater.description: The minimum jitter buffer playout delay in milliseconds configured for the endpoint.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBuffHiWater.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBuffHiWater
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxJBuffHiWater.description: The maximum jitter buffer playout delay in milliseconds configured for the endpoint.

cmqVoIPCallActive3550JShortTermAvg.name: cmqVoIPCallActive3550JShortTermAvg
cmqVoIPCallActive3550JShortTermAvg.description: The instantaneous RFC3550 playout delay buffer in milliseconds to accommodate packet jitter.

cmqVoIPCallActive3550JCallAvg.name: cmqVoIPCallActive3550JCallAvg
cmqVoIPCallActive3550JCallAvg.description: The long-term average of multiple RFC3550 playout delay buffer in milliseconds to accommodate packet jitter.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSignalLvl.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSignalLvl
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxSignalLvl.description: The instantaneous input signal level to the telephony interface (TDM to IP network) that is used by the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107Rscore.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107Rscore
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107Rscore.description: The R-factor based MOS Listening Quality, which is listening quality minus clarity only, with no delay component. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RMosListen.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RMosListen
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RMosListen.description: The MOS Listening Quality Estimate is computed on a running basis with a new value every 10 seconds of received speech. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RScoreConv.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RScoreConv
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RScoreConv.description: The R-factor based MOS Conversation Quality, which is based on loss plus absolute delay. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RMosConv.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RMosConv
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107RMosConv.description: Th MOS Conversation Quality Estimate is computed on a running basis with a new value every 10 seconds of received speech. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107CodecIeBase.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107CodecIeBase
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107CodecIeBase.description: The base Ie score is a factor to calculate IeEff value. It is obtained from G.113 table according to the codec type and is defined in kilobits per second.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107CodecBPL.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107CodecBPL
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107CodecBPL.description: The bpl is a factor to calculate IeEff value. It is obtained from G.113 table according to the codec type and is defined in kilobits per second.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107DefaultR0.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107DefaultR0
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107DefaultR0.description: R0 is a factor based on signal-to-noise ratio which also includes loudness ratings.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107IeEff.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107IeEff
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107IeEff.description: Ie-eff is one of the components to contribute to MOS R-factor calculations, where R-factor is based on ITU-T G.107. Ie is a component which depends on the real-time packet loss, where as Ie-eff stands for equipment impairment factor which includes codec type and packet loss.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107Idd.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107Idd
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPred107Idd.description: Idd is one of the components to contribute to MOS R-factor calculations, where R-factor is based on ITU-T G.107. Idd is a delay impairment factor which depends on the real-time round trip delay and echo.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoAvg.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoAvg
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoAvg.description: The statistical average MOS score of all the previous instantaneous values. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoRecent.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoRecent
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoRecent.description: The most recent MOS score with K-factor input based on frame loss and codec. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoBaseline.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoBaseline
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoBaseline.description: The maximum or codec zero-impairment baseline MOS score of all the previous instantaneous values. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoMin.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoMin
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoMin.description: The statistical minimum MOS score of all the previous instantaneous values. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoNumWin.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoNumWin
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoNumWin.description: A window in 8 seconds of frame loss data required to calculate the MOS estimate.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoBursts.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoBursts
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoBursts.description: The MOS score calculated with K-factor input of consecutive frame loss events, or error bursts. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoFrLoss.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoFrLoss
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoFrLoss.description: The average frame loss count since call start.

cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoVerID.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoVerID
cmqVoIPCallActiveRxPredMosLqoVerID.description: The MOS K-factor version ID, e.g. CVTQ v0.95

cmqVoIPCallActiveTxCodecId.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveTxCodecId
cmqVoIPCallActiveTxCodecId.description: The codec type of the endpoint for the established voice path.

cmqVoIPCallActiveTxVadEnabled.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveTxVadEnabled
cmqVoIPCallActiveTxVadEnabled.description: This flag indicates whether VAD (Voice Activation Detector) is enabled or disabled. A value of 'true' indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqVoIPCallActiveTxTmrCallDur.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveTxTmrCallDur
cmqVoIPCallActiveTxTmrCallDur.description: Duration of transmit path open from this peer to voice gateway for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallActiveTxTmrActSpeechDur.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveTxTmrActSpeechDur
cmqVoIPCallActiveTxTmrActSpeechDur.description: Duration of speech transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallActiveTxSignalLvl.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveTxSignalLvl
cmqVoIPCallActiveTxSignalLvl.description: The instantaneous output signal level from the telephony interface (TDM to IP network) that is used by the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallActiveTxNoiseFloor.name: cmqVoIPCallActiveTxNoiseFloor
cmqVoIPCallActiveTxNoiseFloor.description: The instantaneous noise floor level estimate if VAD is enabled.

cmqCommonCallActiveNRTable.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNRTable
cmqCommonCallActiveNRTable.description: This table is the voice and VoIP extension to the callActiveTable of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice quality information and statistics when noise reduction is applied to the call leg.

cmqCommonCallActiveNREntry.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNREntry
cmqCommonCallActiveNREntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmqCommonCallActiveNRTable. An entry into this table is created when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created which has corresponding callActiveInfoType equals to 'speech'. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

cmqCommonCallActiveNRConnectionId.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNRConnectionId
cmqCommonCallActiveNRConnectionId.description: The global connection identifier for the active leg of the call.

cmqCommonCallActiveNRCallReferenceId.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNRCallReferenceId
cmqCommonCallActiveNRCallReferenceId.description: The call reference ID associates the video call entry and voice call entry of the same endpoint. An audio-only call with a call reference ID of zero will not have a video call entry associated with it, although an audio-only call can also have a reference ID greater than zero.

cmqCommonCallActiveNRCallType.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNRCallType
cmqCommonCallActiveNRCallType.description: This object indicates the call type of the active call leg. tdm(1): TDM call leg. voip (2): VoIP call leg.

cmqCommonCallActiveNREnabledMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNREnabledMic
cmqCommonCallActiveNREnabledMic.description: This flag indicates whether noise reduction is enabled or disabled in the MIC direction. A value of 'true' for this object indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqCommonCallActiveNREnabledEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNREnabledEar
cmqCommonCallActiveNREnabledEar.description: This flag indicates whether noise reduction is enabled or disabled in the ear direction. A value of 'true' for this object indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqCommonCallActiveNRDirMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNRDirMic
cmqCommonCallActiveNRDirMic.description: This object indicates the direction to which noise reduction is applied in the network with respect to MIC. tdm (1): audio stream is from TDM, wan (2): audio stream is from WAN, lan (3): audio stream is from LAN.

cmqCommonCallActiveNRDirEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNRDirEar
cmqCommonCallActiveNRDirEar.description: This object indicates the direction to which noise reduction is applied in the network with respect to ear. tdm (1): audio stream is from TDM, wan (2): audio stream is from WAN, lan (3): audio stream is from LAN.

cmqCommonCallActiveNRLibVer.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNRLibVer
cmqCommonCallActiveNRLibVer.description: The library version of noise reduction module being used.

cmqCommonCallActiveNRIntensity.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNRIntensity
cmqCommonCallActiveNRIntensity.description: The intensity of the noise reduction being applied to audio signals.

cmqCommonCallActivePreNRNoiseFloorEstMic.name: cmqCommonCallActivePreNRNoiseFloorEstMic
cmqCommonCallActivePreNRNoiseFloorEstMic.description: The estimated noise floor level before noise redunction is applied in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallActivePostNRNoiseFloorEstMi.name: cmqCommonCallActivePostNRNoiseFloorEstMic
cmqCommonCallActivePostNRNoiseFloorEstMi.description: The estimated noise floor level after noise redunction is applied in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallActivePreNRNoiseFloorEstEar.name: cmqCommonCallActivePreNRNoiseFloorEstEar
cmqCommonCallActivePreNRNoiseFloorEstEar.description: The estimated noise floor level before noise redunction is applied in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallActivePostNRNoiseFloorEstEa.name: cmqCommonCallActivePostNRNoiseFloorEstEar
cmqCommonCallActivePostNRNoiseFloorEstEa.description: The estimated noise floor level after noise redunction is applied in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPTable.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPTable
cmqCommonCallActiveASPTable.description: This table is the voice and VoIP extension to the callActiveTable of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice quality information and statistics when acoustic shock protection is applied to the call leg.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPEntry.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPEntry
cmqCommonCallActiveASPEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmqCommonCallActiveASPTable. An entry into this table is created when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created which has corresponding callActiveInfoType equals to 'speech'. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPConnectionId.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPConnectionId
cmqCommonCallActiveASPConnectionId.description: The global connection identifier for the active leg of the call.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPCallReferenceId.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPCallReferenceId
cmqCommonCallActiveASPCallReferenceId.description: The call reference ID associates the video call entry and voice call entry of the same endpoint. An audio-only call with a call reference ID of zero will not have a video call entry associated with it, although an audio-only call can also have a reference ID greater than zero.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPCallType.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPCallType
cmqCommonCallActiveASPCallType.description: This object indicates the call type of the active call leg. tdm (1): TDM call leg. voip (2): VoIP call leg.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPEnabledMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPEnabledMic
cmqCommonCallActiveASPEnabledMic.description: This flag indicates whether acoustic shock protection is enabled or disabled in the MIC direction. A value of 'true' for this object indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPEnabledEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPEnabledEar
cmqCommonCallActiveASPEnabledEar.description: This flag indicates whether acoustic shock protection is enabled or disabled in the ear direction. A value of 'true' for this object indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPDirMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPDirMic
cmqCommonCallActiveASPDirMic.description: This object indicates the direction to which acoustic shock protection is applied in the network with respect to MIC. tdm (1): audio stream is from TDM, wan (2): audio stream is from WAN, lan (3): audio stream is from LAN.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPDirEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPDirEar
cmqCommonCallActiveASPDirEar.description: This object indicates the direction to which acoustic shock protection is applied in the network with respect to ear. tdm (1): audio stream is from TDM, wan (2): audio stream is from WAN, lan (3): audio stream is from LAN.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPMode.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPMode
cmqCommonCallActiveASPMode.description: The acoutsic shock protection mode indicates the sensitivity of operation. auto (1): default mode, a trade-off between slow and fast mode, slow (2): slower detection mode, fast (3): faster detection mode, expert (4): expert defined mode.

cmqCommonCallActiveASPVer.name: cmqCommonCallActiveASPVer
cmqCommonCallActiveASPVer.description: The version of acoustic shock protection applied to the audio signal.

cmqCommonCallActiveNumSigASPTriggMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNumSigASPTriggMic
cmqCommonCallActiveNumSigASPTriggMic.description: The number of significant acoustic shock protection triggers which has a duration of greater than 2 seconds and is applied in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveDurSigASPTriggMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveDurSigASPTriggMic
cmqCommonCallActiveDurSigASPTriggMic.description: The cumulative duration of all significant aooustic shock protection triggers in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveTotNumASPTriggMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveTotNumASPTriggMic
cmqCommonCallActiveTotNumASPTriggMic.description: The total number of acoustic shock protection triggers in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveTotASPDurMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveTotASPDurMic
cmqCommonCallActiveTotASPDurMic.description: The total duration of active acoustic shock protection suppression in milliseconds in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveLoudestFreqEstForLong.name: cmqCommonCallActiveLoudestFreqEstForLongEpiMic
cmqCommonCallActiveLoudestFreqEstForLong.description: The loudest frequency estimate for the longest acoustic shock protection episode in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveLongestDurEpiMic.name: cmqCommonCallActiveLongestDurEpiMic
cmqCommonCallActiveLongestDurEpiMic.description: The duration of the longest acoustic shock protection episode in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveNumSigASPTriggEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveNumSigASPTriggEar
cmqCommonCallActiveNumSigASPTriggEar.description: The number of significant acoustic shock protection triggers which has a duration of greater than 2 seconds and is applied in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveDurSigASPTriggEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveDurSigASPTriggEar
cmqCommonCallActiveDurSigASPTriggEar.description: The cumulative duration of all significant aooustic shock protection triggers in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveTotNumASPTriggEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveTotNumASPTriggEar
cmqCommonCallActiveTotNumASPTriggEar.description: The total number of acoustic shock protection triggers in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveTotASPDurEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveTotASPDurEar
cmqCommonCallActiveTotASPDurEar.description: The total duration of active acoustic shock protection suppression in milliseconds in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveLoudestFreqEstForLong.name: cmqCommonCallActiveLoudestFreqEstForLongEpiEar
cmqCommonCallActiveLoudestFreqEstForLong.description: The loudest frequency estimate for the longest acoustic shock protection episode in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallActiveLongestDurEpiEar.name: cmqCommonCallActiveLongestDurEpiEar
cmqCommonCallActiveLongestDurEpiEar.description: The duration of the longest acoustic shock protection episode in the ear direction.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryTable.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryTable
cmqVoIPCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the VoIP extension to the cCallHistoryTable of CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice quality information and statistics for the VoIP call leg.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryEntry.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryEntry
cmqVoIPCallHistoryEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmqVoIPCallHistoryTable. An entry into this table is created when its associated call history entry in the CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created which has corresponding cCallHistoryInfoType equals to 'speech'. The entry is deleted when its associated call history entry in the CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId
cmqVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global connection identifier for the VoIP leg of the call.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryCallReferenceId.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryCallReferenceId
cmqVoIPCallHistoryCallReferenceId.description: The call reference ID associates the video call entry and voice call entry of the same endpoint. An audio-only call with a call reference ID of zero will not have a video call entry associated with it, although an audio-only call can also have a reference ID greater than zero.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCodecId.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCodecId
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCodecId.description: The codec type of the endpoint for the established voice path.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSevConcealRatioPct.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSevConcealRatioPct
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSevConcealRatioPct.description: The ratio of severely concealed seconds to the sum of unimpaired seconds and concealed seconds.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCallConcealRatioPct.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCallConcealRatioPct
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCallConcealRatioPct.description: The ratio of the recent concealment time to recent talk-mode time interval. The talk-mode interval is 3 seconds.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktLossRatioPct.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktLossRatioPct
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktLossRatioPct.description: The ratio of total effective received packet loss to the number of RTP packets expected.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxRoundTripTime.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxRoundTripTime
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxRoundTripTime.description: The round-trip delay is the sum of measured network delay plus transmit and receive endpoint processing delays.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCallDur.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCallDur
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxCallDur.description: Duration of receive path open from this peer to voice gateway for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxVoiceDur.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxVoiceDur
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxVoiceDur.description: Duration of speech received from this peer to voice gateway for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktLossConcealDur.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktLossConcealDur
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktLossConcealDur.description: The sum of error predictive concealment and bad protocol concealment in milliseconds.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntExpected.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntExpected
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntExpected.description: The expected number of packets to be received.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntNotArrived.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntNotArrived
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntNotArrived.description: The expected number of packets minus the number of received packets.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntComfortNoise.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntComfortNoise
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntComfortNoise.description: The number of received comfort noise packets for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntUnusableLate.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntUnusableLate
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntUnusableLate.description: The number of received voice packets that arrived too late to playout with CODEC (Coder/Decoder) during the call.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntDiscarded.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntDiscarded
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntDiscarded.description: The sum of the number of late packets and the number of bad protocol packets.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntEffLoss.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntEffLoss
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPktCntEffLoss.description: The total number of never-arrived packets and the number of discarded packets.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxUnimpairedSecOK.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxUnimpairedSecOK
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxUnimpairedSecOK.description: The cumulative number of seconds during which there was no concealment and is considered as OK seconds.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxConcealSec.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxConcealSec
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxConcealSec.description: The cumulative number of seconds during which there was some concealment.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSevConcealSec.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSevConcealSec
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSevConcealSec.description: The total number of seconds that are severely concealed from the start of the voice stream. A severly concealed second has more than 50ms of concealment.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufMode.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufMode
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufMode.description: The jitter buffer mode configured for the endpoint. adaptive(1): an adaptive size algorithm for jitter buffer, fixed (2): a fixed size algorithm for jitter buffer, unknown (3): an unknown size algorithm for jitter buffer, disabled (4): no jitter buffer is configured.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufNomDelay.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufNomDelay
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufNomDelay.description: The nominal jitter buffer playout delay in milliseconds configured for the endpoint.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufDlyNow.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufDlyNow
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufDlyNow.description: The playout delay buffer in milliseconds to accommodate interarrival jitter. The interarrival jitter is the network arrival jitter between consecutive frames measured at the receiver.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufLowWater.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufLowWater
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBufLowWater.description: The minimum jitter buffer playout delay in milliseconds configured for the endpoint.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBuffHiWater.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBuffHiWater
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxJBuffHiWater.description: The maximum jitter buffer playout delay in milliseconds configured for the endpoint.

cmqVoIPCallHistory3550JShortTermAvg.name: cmqVoIPCallHistory3550JShortTermAvg
cmqVoIPCallHistory3550JShortTermAvg.description: The instantaneous RFC3550 playout delay buffer in milliseconds to accommodate packet jitter.

cmqVoIPCallHistory3550JCallAvg.name: cmqVoIPCallHistory3550JCallAvg
cmqVoIPCallHistory3550JCallAvg.description: The long-term average of multiple RFC3550 playout delay buffer in milliseconds to accommodate packet jitter.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSignalLvl.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSignalLvl
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxSignalLvl.description: The instantaneous input signal level to the telephony interface (TDM to IP network) that is used by the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107Rscore.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107Rscore
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107Rscore.description: The R-factor based MOS Listening Quality, which is listening quality minus clarity only, with no delay component. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RMosListen.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RMosListen
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RMosListen.description: The MOS Listening Quality Estimate is computed on a running basis with a new value every 10 seconds of received speech. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RScoreConv.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RScoreConv
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RScoreConv.description: The R-factor based MOS Conversation Quality, which is based on loss plus absolute delay. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RMosConv.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RMosConv
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107RMosConv.description: Th MOS Conversation Quality Estimate is computed on a running basis with a new value every 10 seconds of received speech. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107CodecIeBase.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107CodecIeBase
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107CodecIeBase.description: The base Ie score is a factor to calculate IeEff value. It is obtained from G.113 table according to the codec type and is defined in killobits per second.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107CodecBPL.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107CodecBPL
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107CodecBPL.description: The bpl is a factor to calculate IeEff value. It is obtained from G.113 table according to the codec type and is defined in kilobits per second.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107DefaultR0.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107DefaultR0
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107DefaultR0.description: R0 is a factor based on signal-to-noise ratio which also includes loudness ratings.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107IeEff.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107IeEff
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107IeEff.description: Ie-eff is one of the components to contribute to MOS R-factor calculations, where R-factor is based on ITU-T G.107. Ie is a component which depends on the real-time packet loss, where as Ie-eff stands for equipment impairment factor which includes codec type and packet loss.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107Idd.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107Idd
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPred107Idd.description: Idd is one of the components to contribute to MOS R-factor calculations, where R-factor is based on ITU-T G.107. Idd is a delay impairment factor which depends on the real-time round trip delay and echo.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoAvg.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoAvg
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoAvg.description: The statistical average MOS score of all the previous instantaneous values. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoRecent.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoRecent
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoRecent.description: The most recent MOS score with K-factor input based on frame loss and codec. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoBaseline.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoBaseline
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoBaseline.description: The maximum or codec zero-impairment baseline MOS score of all the previous instantaneous values. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoMin.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoMin
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoMin.description: The statistical minimum MOS score of all the previous instantaneous values. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoNumWin.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoNumWin
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoNumWin.description: A window in 8 seconds of frame loss data required to calculate the MOS estimate.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoBursts.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoBursts
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoBursts.description: The MOS score calculated with K-factor input of consecutive frame loss events, or error bursts. A value of 0 indicates an invalid score and a positive value indicates a valid score.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoFrLoss.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoFrLoss
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoFrLoss.description: The average frame loss count since call start.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoVerID.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoVerID
cmqVoIPCallHistoryRxPredMosLqoVerID.description: The MOS K-factor version ID, e.g. CVTQ v0.95

cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxCodecId.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxCodecId
cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxCodecId.description: The codec type of the endpoint for the established voice path.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxVadEnabled.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxVadEnabled
cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxVadEnabled.description: This flag indicates whether VAD (Voice Activation Detector) is enabled or disabled. A value of 'true' indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxTmrCallDur.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxTmrCallDur
cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxTmrCallDur.description: Duration of transmit path open from this peer to voice gateway for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxTmrActSpeechDur.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxTmrActSpeechDur
cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxTmrActSpeechDur.description: Duration of speech transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxSignalLvl.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxSignalLvl
cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxSignalLvl.description: The instantaneous output signal level from the telephony interface (TDM to IP network) that is used by the call leg.

cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxNoiseFloor.name: cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxNoiseFloor
cmqVoIPCallHistoryTxNoiseFloor.description: The instantaneous noise floor level estimate if VAD is enabled.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNRTable.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNRTable
cmqCommonCallHistoryNRTable.description: This table is the voice and VoIP extension to the cCallHistoryTable of CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice quality information and statistics when noise reduction is applied to the call leg.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNREntry.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNREntry
cmqCommonCallHistoryNREntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmqCommonCallHistoryTable. An entry into this table is created when its associated call history entry in the CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created which has corresponding cCallHistoryInfoType equals to 'speech'. The entry is deleted when its associated call history entry in the CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNRConnectionId.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNRConnectionId
cmqCommonCallHistoryNRConnectionId.description: The global connection identifier for the history leg of the call.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNRCallReferenceId.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNRCallReferenceId
cmqCommonCallHistoryNRCallReferenceId.description: The call reference ID associates the video call entry and voice call entry of the same endpoint. An audio-only call with a call reference ID of zero will not have a video call entry associated with it, although an audio-only call can also have a reference ID greater than zero.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNRCallType.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNRCallType
cmqCommonCallHistoryNRCallType.description: This object indicates the call type of the history call leg. tdm (1): TDM call leg. voip (2): VoIP call leg.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNREnabledMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNREnabledMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryNREnabledMic.description: This flag indicates whether noise reduction is enabled or disabled in the MIC direction. A value of 'true' for this object indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNREnabledEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNREnabledEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryNREnabledEar.description: This flag indicates whether noise reduction is enabled or disabled in the ear direction. A value of 'true' for this object indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNRDirMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNRDirMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryNRDirMic.description: This object indicates the direction to which noise reduction is applied in the network with respect to MIC. tdm (1): audio stream is from TDM, wan (2): audio stream is from WAN, lan (3): audio stream is from LAN.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNRDirEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNRDirEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryNRDirEar.description: This object indicates the direction to which noise reduction is applied in the network with respect to ear. tdm (1): audio stream is from TDM, wan (2): audio stream is from WAN, lan (3): audio stream is from LAN.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNRLibVer.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNRLibVer
cmqCommonCallHistoryNRLibVer.description: The library version of noise reduction module being used.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNRIntensity.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNRIntensity
cmqCommonCallHistoryNRIntensity.description: The intensity of the noise reduction being applied to audio signals.

cmqCommonCallHistoryPreNRNoiseFloorEstMi.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryPreNRNoiseFloorEstMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryPreNRNoiseFloorEstMi.description: The estimated noise floor level before noise redunction is applied in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryPostNRNoiseFloorEstM.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryPostNRNoiseFloorEstMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryPostNRNoiseFloorEstM.description: The estimated noise floor level after noise redunction is applied in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryPreNRNoiseFloorEstEa.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryPreNRNoiseFloorEstEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryPreNRNoiseFloorEstEa.description: The estimated noise floor level before noise redunction is applied in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryPostNRNoiseFloorEstE.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryPostNRNoiseFloorEstEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryPostNRNoiseFloorEstE.description: The estimated noise floor level after noise redunction is applied in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPTable.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPTable
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPTable.description: This table is the voice and VoIP extension to the cCallHistoryTable of CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice quality information and statistics when acoustic shock protection is applied to the call leg.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEntry.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEntry
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmqCommonCallHistoryTable. An entry into this table is created when its associated call history entry in the CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created which has corresponding cCallHistoryInfoType equals to 'speech'. The entry is deleted when its associated call history entry in the CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPConnectionId.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPConnectionId
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPConnectionId.description: The global connection identifier for the history leg of the call.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPCallReferenceId.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPCallReferenceId
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPCallReferenceId.description: The call reference ID associates the video call entry and voice call entry of the same endpoint. An audio-only call with a call reference ID of zero will not have a video call entry associated with it, although an audio-only call can also have a reference ID greater than zero.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPCallType.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPCallType
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPCallType.description: This object indicates the call type of the history call leg. tdm (1): TDM call leg voip (2): VoIP call leg.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEnabledMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEnabledMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEnabledMic.description: This flag indicates whether acoustic shock protection is enabled or disabled in the MIC direction. A value of 'true' for this object indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEnabledEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEnabledEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPEnabledEar.description: This flag indicates whether acoustic shock protection is enabled or disabled in the ear direction. A value of 'true' for this object indicates enabled and a value of 'false' indicates disabled. Default is disabled.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPDirMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPDirMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPDirMic.description: This object indicates the direction to which acoustic shock protection is applied in the network with respect to MIC. tdm (1): audio stream is from TDM, wan (2): audio stream is from WAN, lan (3): audio stream is from LAN.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPDirEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPDirEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPDirEar.description: This object indicates the direction to which acoustic shock protection is applied in the network with respect to ear. tdm (1): audio stream is from TDM, wan (2): audio stream is from WAN, lan (3): audio stream is from LAN.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPMode.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPMode
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPMode.description: The acoutsic shock protection mode indicates the sensitivity of operation. auto (1): default mode, a trade-off between slow and fast mode, slow (2): slower detection mode, fast (3): faster detection mode, expert (4): expert defined mode.

cmqCommonCallHistoryASPVer.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryASPVer
cmqCommonCallHistoryASPVer.description: The version of acoutsic shock protection applied to audio signals.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNumSigASPTriggMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNumSigASPTriggMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryNumSigASPTriggMic.description: The number of significant acoustic shock protection triggers which has a duration of greater than 2 seconds and is applied in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryDurSigASPTriggMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryDurSigASPTriggMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryDurSigASPTriggMic.description: The cumulative duration of all significant aooustic shock protection triggers in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryTotNumASPTriggMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryTotNumASPTriggMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryTotNumASPTriggMic.description: The total number of acoustic shock protection triggers in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryTotASPDurMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryTotASPDurMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryTotASPDurMic.description: The total duration of acoustic shock protection suppression in milliseconds in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryLoudestFreqEstForLon.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryLoudestFreqEstForLongEpiMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryLoudestFreqEstForLon.description: The loudest frequency estimate for the longest acoustic shock protection episode in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryLongestDurEpiMic.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryLongestDurEpiMic
cmqCommonCallHistoryLongestDurEpiMic.description: The duration of the longest acoustic shock protection episode in the MIC direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryNumSigASPTriggEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryNumSigASPTriggEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryNumSigASPTriggEar.description: The number of significant acoustic shock protection triggers which has a duration of greater than 2 seconds and is applied in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryDurSigASPTriggEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryDurSigASPTriggEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryDurSigASPTriggEar.description: The cumulative duration of all significant aooustic shock protection triggers in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryTotNumASPTriggEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryTotNumASPTriggEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryTotNumASPTriggEar.description: The total number of acoustic shock protection triggers in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryTotASPDurEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryTotASPDurEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryTotASPDurEar.description: The total duration of acoustic shock protection suppression in milliseconds in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryLoudestFreqEstForLon.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryLoudestFreqEstForLongEpiEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryLoudestFreqEstForLon.description: The loudest frequency estimate for the longest acoustic shock protection episode in the ear direction.

cmqCommonCallHistoryLongestDurEpiEar.name: cmqCommonCallHistoryLongestDurEpiEar
cmqCommonCallHistoryLongestDurEpiEar.description: The duration of the longest acoustic shock protection episode in the ear direction.

cmqVideoCallActiveTable.name: cmqVideoCallActiveTable
cmqVideoCallActiveTable.description: This table is the video extension to the call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains video quality information for the VoIP call leg.

cmqVideoCallActiveEntry.name: cmqVideoCallActiveEntry
cmqVideoCallActiveEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmqVideoCallActiveTable. An entry is added to the table when the below conditions are met: 1. A call active entry in callActiveTable of the IETF Dial Control MIB with video callActiveInfoType is created. 2. An entry in cVideoCommonActiveTable of the Cisco Video Session MIB is created whose cVideoCommonActiveCallType is pointToPointCall, conferenceCall, or monitoredCall. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in callActiveTable of the IETF Dial Control MIB is deleted.

cmqVideoCallActiveConnectionId.name: cmqVideoCallActiveConnectionId
cmqVideoCallActiveConnectionId.description: The global connection identifier for the video leg of the call.

cmqVideoCallActiveCallReferenceId.name: cmqVideoCallActiveCallReferenceId
cmqVideoCallActiveCallReferenceId.description: The call reference ID associates the video call entry and voice call entry of the same endpoint.

cmqVideoCallActiveRxMOSInstant.name: cmqVideoCallActiveRxMOSInstant
cmqVideoCallActiveRxMOSInstant.description: Instantaneous aggregated MOS in the receive direction, where 0 is an invalid score and the lowest score starts with 1. A value of 100 indicates the best video quality.

cmqVideoCallActiveRxCompressDegradeInsta.name: cmqVideoCallActiveRxCompressDegradeInstant
cmqVideoCallActiveRxCompressDegradeInsta.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX instantaneous MOS) due to the initial compression of video at an end point introduced by a video encoder.

cmqVideoCallActiveRxNetworkDegradeInstan.name: cmqVideoCallActiveRxNetworkDegradeInstant
cmqVideoCallActiveRxNetworkDegradeInstan.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX instantaneous MOS) due to network factors, such as jitter, delay and packet loss.

cmqVideoCallActiveRxTransscodeDegradeIns.name: cmqVideoCallActiveRxTransscodeDegradeInstant
cmqVideoCallActiveRxTransscodeDegradeIns.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX instantaneous MOS) due to the transcoding, including transrating, of a video stream.

cmqVideoCallActiveRxMOSAverage.name: cmqVideoCallActiveRxMOSAverage
cmqVideoCallActiveRxMOSAverage.description: Average aggregated MOS in the receive direction since the beginning of the video session. 0 indicates an invalid score and the lowest score starts with 1. A value of 100 indicates the best video quality.

cmqVideoCallActiveRxCompressDegradeAvera.name: cmqVideoCallActiveRxCompressDegradeAverage
cmqVideoCallActiveRxCompressDegradeAvera.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX average MOS) due to the initial compression of video at an end point introduced by a video encoder.

cmqVideoCallActiveRxNetworkDegradeAverag.name: cmqVideoCallActiveRxNetworkDegradeAverage
cmqVideoCallActiveRxNetworkDegradeAverag.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX average MOS) due to network factors, such as jitter, delay and packet loss.

cmqVideoCallActiveRxTransscodeDegradeAve.name: cmqVideoCallActiveRxTransscodeDegradeAverage
cmqVideoCallActiveRxTransscodeDegradeAve.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX average MOS) due to the transcoding, including transrating, of a video stream.

cmqVideoCallHistoryTable.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryTable
cmqVideoCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the video extension to the call history table of CISCO-DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains video quality information for the VoIP call leg.

cmqVideoCallHistoryEntry.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryEntry
cmqVideoCallHistoryEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmqVideoCallHistoryTable. An entry is added to the table when the below conditions are met: 1. A call history entry in cCallHistoryTable of the Cisco Dial Control MIB with video cCallHistoryInfoType is created. 2. An entry in cVideoCommonActiveTable of the Cisco Video Session MIB is created whose cVideoCommonActiveCallType is pointToPointCall, conferenceCall, or monitoredCall. The entry is deleted when its associated call history entriy in cCallHistoryTable of the Cisco Dial Control MIB is deleted.

cmqVideoCallHistoryConnectionId.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryConnectionId
cmqVideoCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global connection identifier for the video leg of the call.

cmqVideoCallHistoryCallReferenceId.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryCallReferenceId
cmqVideoCallHistoryCallReferenceId.description: The call reference ID associates the video call entry and voice call entry of the same endpoint.

cmqVideoCallHistoryRxMOSAverage.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryRxMOSAverage
cmqVideoCallHistoryRxMOSAverage.description: Average aggregated MOS in the receive direction since the beginning of the video session. 0 indicates an invalid score and the lowest score starts with 1. A value of 100 indicates the best video quality.

cmqVideoCallHistoryRxCompressDegradeAver.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryRxCompressDegradeAverage
cmqVideoCallHistoryRxCompressDegradeAver.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX average MOS) due to the initial compression of video at an end point introduced by a video encoder.

cmqVideoCallHistoryRxNetworkDegradeAvera.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryRxNetworkDegradeAverage
cmqVideoCallHistoryRxNetworkDegradeAvera.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX average MOS) due to network factors, such as jitter, delay and packet loss.

cmqVideoCallHistoryRxTransscodeDegradeAv.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryRxTransscodeDegradeAverage
cmqVideoCallHistoryRxTransscodeDegradeAv.description: The percentage of quality loss (indicated by RX average MOS) due to the transcoding, including transrating, of a video stream.

ciscoMediaQualityMIBCompliance.name: ciscoMediaQualityMIBCompliance
ciscoMediaQualityMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the SNMP entities that implement ciscoMediaQualityMIB module.

cmqVoiceCallActiveGroup.name: cmqVoiceCallActiveGroup
cmqVoiceCallActiveGroup.description: The collection of objects that provide voice quality statistics for active voice calls.

cmqVoiceCallHistoryGroup.name: cmqVoiceCallHistoryGroup
cmqVoiceCallHistoryGroup.description: The collection of objects that provide voice quality statistics for history voice calls.

cmqVideoCallActiveGroup.name: cmqVideoCallActiveGroup
cmqVideoCallActiveGroup.description: The collection of objects that provide video quality statistics for active video calls.

cmqVideoCallHistoryGroup.name: cmqVideoCallHistoryGroup
cmqVideoCallHistoryGroup.description: The collection of objects that provide video quality statistics for history video calls.
